718230f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park - Harlem Mere.
718230f-a.text:
(1)
Central Park: The Lake, view south from the northern end, showing
the midtown skyline between Fifth and Eighth Avenues, from
the Hotel Plaza to the General Motors Building.
June 28, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, four years later. The gigantic R. C. A. Building, at
Radio City, has been added to the skyline.
June 24, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

718226f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park - Harlem Mere.
718226f-a.text:
Centrsl Park: A southeastern view across the Harlem Mere to show
buildings on Fifth Ave. The two prominent structures at the left and
center are: the Daughters of Israel Building and the Fifth Ave. Hospital.
May 18, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

718228f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park - Harlem Mere.
718228f-a.text:
Central Park: Harlem Mere, in the northeastern corner of the Park;
the view is north from Mount St. Vincent. The southern end of
Lenox Avenue is behind the boathouse. The older part of the
Cathedral of St. John the Divine, on Morningside Heights, is
shown in the left background.
About 1925.
Ewing Galloway.
NO REPRODUCT1ONS.
